UML:TaggedValue.value: Administrators can always access all services, service providers and developers can always access their services, but editing may result in the service obtaining a disapproved/unusable state.
Developers and Service Providers receive notifications when their services are edited by administrators. They may specify what kind of notifications they want to receive.

UML:UseCase.name: Becoming administrator, service provider, or developer

UML:TaggedValue.value: Registered users, via e-mail or web interface, can requested to obtain a desired role, then an existing administrator checks if the user has provided all of the needed personal information for the role, checks the correctness of the info - e-mails, phone numbers, etc. and finally approves or disapproves the request and eventually assigns the role to the user.

Service provider or developer can make their services invisible/unusable to the end users, or completely remove them from the system.
Administrators can make a service visible or invisible/unusable to the end users, with an appropriate notification to the corresponding service provider or developer.
